raw_data.title: CAD Draftsman / Designer
raw_data.description: Design assistance for a proposal and/or project. Implement and develop project plans and specifications,  or, as required, refine or create site specific CAD drawings. If necessary, field detail and provide site specific drawings for approval.  Assist with product shop drawing coordination, project manuals, and warranty information.

raw_data.title: Contract Adminstrator
raw_data.description: Responsible for processing contract and change order requirements including contract letters and other communications and notices, insurance requests and payroll adminstration.

raw_data.title: Equipment Operator
raw_data.description: Operating machinery such as forklifts, skid steers, bobcats and excavators to perform tasks on the construction site.  Tasks can include loading, unloading and moving materials, land excavation and grading, loading, moving and unloading of land, cement or stones, digging holes and placing large objects

raw_data.title: Foreman
raw_data.description: Responsible for the daily operations at the construction site including creating schedules, coordinating daily tasks, overseeing quality of work, Communicating site rules and safety procedures and enforcing those rules, reporting progress to supervisors and working with customers on site.  Onsite construction duties can include erecting and repairing fence, creating the lays out of the fence line and marking positions for postholes.  Digging postholes, pouring concrete, aligning posts, attaching fence-rail support to post, attaching rails or tension wire along bottoms of posts to form fencing frame, stretching wire, wire mesh, or chain link fencing between posts and attaching fencing to frame. Assembling gate and fastening it in position. Erecting alternate panel, basket weave, and louvered fences. May also weld metal parts together.

raw_data.title: Facility Security Officer
raw_data.description: Responsible for creating, executing and monitoring the security policies, procedures and practices in compliance with the project specific requirements.  Ensures COMSEC requirements and procedures are implemented and followed.   Conduct security briefings, trainings and debriefings.  Administer the processing of clearances and visitor requests.  Maintain all records in compliance with security protocols and procedures.  Ensure all proper paperwork and clearances are maintained including specific job site vetting and personnel approvals.

raw_data.title: Skilled Laborer
raw_data.description: Assists the foreman with completing the daily tasks required on the construction site.  May be required to operate power tools, drills, jackhammers, and other heavy machinery.  Will dig postholes and assist in the pouring of concrete.  Responsible for moving materials to the worksite and ensuring all tools, machinery and equipment are safely setup.  Will ensure the worksite is clean and safe and will obey the safety requirements of the jobsite.  Will perform site and equipment inspections prior to performing work.  Will attend onsite meetings and workshops as required.

raw_data.title: Access Control/Operator Manager
raw_data.description: Oversee the planning, management, and coordination of access control related operations.  Consult in design and implementation of access control, gate operators, and operable crash rated systems.  Formulate and oversee new installations.  Provide customer with technical expertise and support.

raw_data.title: Project Manager
raw_data.description: Oversee project from start to finish.  Prioritize and meet deadlines, establish cost budgets, monitor project cost and profit, negotiate and administer subcontracts, attend project meetings/calls.  Communicate with client and provide ongoing support, prepare bids and estimates for change order work, prepare the monthly billings and establish, monitor and update schedules for project.

raw_data.title: Safety Director
raw_data.description: Attend site specific safety meetings.  Complete project specific safety forms and AHA reports.  Routinely inspect the job site, machinery and safety equipment in order to identify and correct potential hazards and to ensure safety regulation compliance.  Perform audits of job sites.  Conduct weekly toolbox talks, or daily toolbox talks if contractually required.  Conduct more in-depth monthly safety meetings.  Setup and monitor safety and accident prevention measures/plans.  Perform comprehensive, in-depth investigations of all injury and loss incidents, identify casual factors, develop and implement measures to prevent reoccurrence.

raw_data.title: Project Executive / Senior Project Manager
raw_data.description: Responsible for developing strategic program and project goals and monitoring program and project performance.   Track projects, along with Project Manager, from concept to project completion.   Overseeing all projects and conforming with plans and specifications, meeting all schedules.  Coordinate with Project Manager to establish cost budgets, monitor project cost and profit, negotiate and administer subcontracts, attend project meetings/calls.  Provide support to the Project Manager to prepare bids and estimates for change order work and issue monthly billings.

raw_data.title: Project Superintendent
raw_data.description: Provides on-site coordination of all phases of construction projects.  Will lead and manage the on-site construction team and supervise the work conducted by subcontractors and direct labor.  Will be responsible for ordering, receiving, inspecting and ensuring the proper storage of all project related equipment and materials.  They will ensure work is being completed per specifications and on time.  The Project Superintendent will be responsible for the compliance of site safety regulations, will conduct inspections with customer and will ensure quality standards are met.

raw_data.title: Technician Assistant
raw_data.description: Assist in the installation and repair of access control and automatic gate systems.

raw_data.title: Technician
raw_data.description: Communicate with customer, order parts, diagnose problems, install, maintain & repair access control and automatic gate systems to include: wedge barrier, hydraulic bollards, crash barrier arms, non-rated traffic arms, gate operator systems, turnstiles, guard booth installation services, pre-fabricated building installation, keypads, card readers, remote receivers, telephone entry systems, gate operators of all makes and models, crash rated barriers and bollards.

raw_data.title: Welder / Fabricator
raw_data.description: Able to fabricate and manufature metal parts and products.  Producing clean, polished welds.  Reads blueprints and sketches in order to execute jobs and tasks to specification.  Proficient in cutting, grinding, polishing, reading blueprints and detailing.
